import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['adjclose'], color='blue')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Adjusted Close Price')
    ax.set_title('What is the trend of the stock prices over time?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['volume'] = pd.to_numeric(data['volume'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['volume'])]
    plt.hist(data['volume'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['volume'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.xlabel('Volume')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of daily trading volumes?')
    plt.legend()
    plt.tight_layout()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    ax.scatter(data['open'], data['close'], alpha=0.5, color='blue')
    ax.axvline(x=data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Open: {data['open'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.axhline(y=data['close'].mean(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean Close: {data['close'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.set_xlabel('Open')
    ax.set_ylabel('Close')
    ax.set_title('What is the relationship between the opening and closing prices?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data = data.set_index('date')
    data = data[['high', 'low']]
    ax = data.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(12, 8), width=0.8, color=['#FFA07A', '#20B2AA'])
    ax.axhline(y=data['high'].max(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Highest Price: {data["high"].max():,.2f}')
    ax.axhline(y=data['low'].min(), color='green', linestyle='--', label=f'Lowest Price: {data["low"].min():,.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the highest and lowest price of the stock during the given time period?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    data['daily_return'] = data['adjclose'].pct_change()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['daily_return'], color='blue')
    ax.axhline(y=data['daily_return'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Mean: {data['daily_return'].mean():.2f}")
    ax.legend(loc='best')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Daily Return')
    ax.set_title('What is the average daily return of the stock?')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
